From: Mandriva (rebased by Arena Agent for glibc 2.43)
Date: 2026-06-04
Subject: [PATCH] Mandriva: do not define __va_arg_pack for clang

Clang fakes __GNUC__=4 but does not implement __builtin_va_arg_pack.
Upstream glibc 2.43 acknowledges this in a comment at misc/sys/cdefs.h
line 205 but still defines the macros unconditionally when __GNUC_PREREQ
(4,3) holds.  Gate on !defined(__clang__) so clang builds do not break.

Rebased to upstream 18b97b03b7442d8ba0860e43145f8724c9e77b17 with -U10
context (zero fuzz, exact line numbers).

--- a/misc/sys/cdefs.h
+++ b/misc/sys/cdefs.h
@@ -627,21 +627,21 @@
 #  define __extern_always_inline extern __always_inline
 # endif
 #endif
 
 #ifdef __extern_always_inline
 # define __fortify_function __extern_always_inline __attribute_artificial__
 #endif
 
 /* GCC 4.3 and above allow passing all anonymous arguments of an
    __extern_always_inline function to some other vararg function.  */
-#if __GNUC_PREREQ (4,3)
+#if __GNUC_PREREQ (4,3) && !defined(__clang__)
 # define __va_arg_pack() __builtin_va_arg_pack ()
 # define __va_arg_pack_len() __builtin_va_arg_pack_len ()
 #endif
 
 /* It is possible to compile containing GCC extensions even if GCC is
    run in pedantic mode if the uses are carefully marked using the
    `__extension__' keyword.  But this is not generally available before
    version 2.8.  */
 #if !(__GNUC_PREREQ (2,8) || defined __clang__)
 # define __extension__		/* Ignore */
